record_data.record_narrative_name: RATE SCHEDULE FOR THE SALE, ASSIGNMENT, OR TRANSFER OF TRANSMISSION RIGHTS
record_data.record_plain_text: Portland General Electric Company FERC Electric Tariff Second Revised Volume No. 12 Portland General Electric Company FERC Electric Tariff Second Revised Volume No. 12 Rate Schedule for the Sale, Assignment, or Transfer of Transmission Rights DEFINITIONS 1.1Commission: The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. 1.2Customer: Any person that executes an Umbrella Service Agreement for service under this tariff. 1.3Transmission Rights: Wholesale Merchant Function s rights to the use of the transmission system of a non-jurisdictional transmitting utility for which the transmission provider does not play the intermediary role in secondary market transmission transactions as contemplated under the reforms that the Commission adopted in Order No. 890, et. seq.. 1.4Umbrella Service Agreement: The agreement and any amendments or supplements thereto entered into by Customer. 1.5Wholesale Merchant Function: Those PGE employees whose responsibilities include sale for resale, or purchase for resale, of electric energy in interstate commerce and the sale, assignment or transfer of Transmission Rights. 2.0 GENERAL PURPOSE The purpose of the Rate Schedule is to provide for the sale, assignment, or transfer of Transmission Rights by Portland General Electric Company s ( PGE ) Wholesale Merchant Function This Rate Schedule shall become effective on the date the Federal Regulatory Energy Commission allows it to become effective. 2.1 Duration This Rate Schedule shall continue in effect until terminated or changed and such termination or change becomes effective in accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements. 2.2 Services To Be Rendered The Wholesale Merchant Function may sell, assign, or transfer to a customer desiring to take transmission rights under this Rate Schedule ( Customer ), pursuant to an agreement negotiated between them, all or a portion of the Wholesale Merchant Function s rights to the use of the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility system that the Wholesale Merchant Function has reserved for its own use under a service agreement with the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility or has acquired from another customer. Customer must be an eligible customer under the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility s open access transmission tariff or other rate schedules pursuant to which the Transmission Rights to be transferred to Customer were originally obtained from the transmission provider. 2.3 Sale of Transmission Rights The Wholesale Merchant Function may sell Transmission Rights which the Wholesale Merchant Function has reserved for its own use from the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility. The Wholesale Merchant Function may sell, assign or transfer such Transmission Rights at the price provided in Part 2.5.1 below. 2.4 Terms and Conditions 2.4.1 Except as to price and creditworthiness, the terms and conditions under which the Wholesale Merchant Function will sell, assign, or transfer such Transmission Rights to Customer shall be the terms and conditions governing the original grant by the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility of Transmission Rights. 2.4.2 Should the Customer s creditworthiness, financial responsibility, or performance viability become unsatisfactory to PGE in PGE s sole, reasonably exercised discretion, PGE may require Customer to promptly deliver (i) its annual audited consolidated financial statements, or those of its Guarantor (as defined herein), certified by independent public accountants; or (ii) a copy of the Form 10-K or the annual report for such party, or its Guarantor, containing audited financial statements for the most recently ended financial year; or (iii) the most recent copy of its quarterly financial statements or 10-Q for such party, or its Guarantor, prepared in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, consistently applied. For purposes of this Umbrella Service Agreement, Guarantor shall mean an entity that provides credit support for the obligations of the Customer issued for the full duration of all transactions under this contract or otherwise. PGE may also require the Customer to provide, at the Customer s option, either (i) the posting of a letter of credit, (ii) a cash prepayment, (iii) a guarantee, or (iv) the posting of other acceptable collateral or security by the Customer. If the Customer fails to provide such satisfactory assurances of its ability to perform a transaction hereunder within three (3) business days of demand therefore, PGE (in addition to exercising any and all remedies available at law or in equity, expressly inclusive of, but not limited to withholding, setting off against or recouping from amounts otherwise due) (i) may suspend performance of the transaction, or (ii) immediately terminate the transaction, calculating, consistent with this agreement and any confirmation agreement, the amount of its costs, expenses, and losses incurred due to the Customer s inability to perform, and presenting the Customer with a demand therefore which must be paid within three (3) business days of receipt. In determining whether the Customer has provided satisfactory assurances and in determining the action to be taken, PGE may suspend performance or terminate the transaction without making a filing at FERC. 2.5 Compensations The Wholesale Merchant Function shall sell, assign, or transfer any Transmission Rights pursuant to this Rate Schedule to Customer at rates established by agreement between the Wholesale Merchant Function and Customer. 2.6 Modifications PGE may unilaterally apply to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this Rate Schedule under section 205 of the Federal Power Act and the regulations promulgated under that Act. Portland General Electric Company Form of Umbrella Service Agreement For the Sale, Assignment, or Transfer of Transmission Rights This Service Agreement, dated as of ___________________, is entered into, by and between Portland General Electric Company ( PGE ) and ____________________ ( Customer ). PGE and Customer may also be referred to collectively as Parties, and individually as Party. PGE agrees to furnish and Customer agrees to purchase Transmission Rights pursuant to the terms and conditions of PGE s Rate Schedule for the Sale, Assignment, or Transfer of Transmission Rights as revised from time to time pursuant to filings with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. 1.0 Customer has been determined by PGE to be an eligible customer under the open access transmission tariff or other rate schedule pursuant to which the Transmission Rights to be transferred to Customer were originally obtained from a non-jurisdictional transmitting utility. 2.0 This Agreement shall extend for __________________ from the date hereof, and shall continue in force thereafter until and unless canceled upon a minimum of 60 days prior written notice by either Party to the other Party. However, sales already entered into prior to notice of termination shall continue for the duration of the sale. 3.0At the time of entering into a sale, assignment or transfer of Transmission Rights, the Parties shall identify and document the agreed to type of transmission service to be provided hereunder. 4.0For each transaction, Customer shall pay to PGE such charges as are agreed upon orally, or, if expressly required by either Party with respect to a particular transaction, in writing. Each party consents to the recording of all telephone conversations relating to transactions under this agreement between its trading and marketing employees and the trading and marketing employees of the other Party, and that any such recordings will be retained in confidence, secured from improper access, and may be submitted in evidence in any proceeding or action relating to this agreement. With respect to such recordings, each Party waives any further notice of such monitoring or recording, and agrees to notify its employees of such monitoring or recording and to obtain any necessary consent of such employees. The recording, and the terms and conditions described therein, shall be the controlling evidence of the Parties agreement with respect to a particular transaction. 5.0 Any notice made to or by either Party regarding this Service Agreement shall be made to the representative of the other Party as indicated below.
